  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scaling up Ebola Response Mechanisms &#x2013; Providing Psychosocial support for Children Affected by Ebola</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will seek to reduce the transmission of Ebola virus in the affected districts and communities through scaling up effective, evidence-based outbreak control measures. 

It will help create public awareness about Ebola Virus Disease (EVD), the risk factors for its transmission, and its prevention and control. It will provide psychosocial support for EVD-affected individuals and families through the Ministry of Social Welfare, Gender and Children Affairs; ensure effective coordination; and strengthen early detection, reporting and referral of suspected cases through active monitoring and outbreak investigation.</narrative>
  </description>
